in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh de Bolebec Baron of Whitchurch was born about 1115, in Aylesbury, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Walter de Bolebec, was 40 and his mother, Hawise, was 18. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Margaret De Montfichet. He died after 1165, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1115–Aft 1165":"umbes 1115–pärast 1165","1115–1165":"1115–1165","1142–1188":"1142–1188","1162–Male":"1162–Surnud","1164–1245":"1164–1245","–Female":"Surnud","1075–1164":"1075–1164","1099–Female":"1099–Surnud","Abt 1162":"umbes 1162","1115":"1115","Aft 1165":"pärast 1165","1245":"1245","1188":"1188","1099":"1099","1165":"1165","1164":"1164","1142":"1142","Abt 1115":"umbes 1115","1075":"1075","1162":"1162","Aylesbury, Buckinghamshire, England":"Aylesbury, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Styford, Northumberland, England":"Styford, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whitchurch, Buckinghamshire, England":"Whitchurch, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", , , England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1115–Aft 1165":"noin 1115–1165 jälkeen","1115–1165":"1115–1165","1142–1188":"1142–1188","1162–Male":"1162–Kuollut","1164–1245":"1164–1245","–Female":"Kuollut","1075–1164":"1075–1164","1099–Female":"1099–Kuollut","Abt 1162":"noin 1162","1115":"1115","Aft 1165":"1165 jälkeen","1245":"1245","1188":"1188","1099":"1099","1165":"1165","1164":"1164","1142":"1142","Abt 111